header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS INVITATIONAL AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Western Kentucky 76, Ball State 66
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Courtney Lee scored 17 points and junior guard Tyrone Brazelton scored a career-high 16 to lead Western Kentucky past Ball State 76-66 in the final round of the Las Vegas Invitational Saturday night. Lee went 6-of-6 from the free-throw line, while Brazelton went 5-of-6 from the charity stripe. Also for the Hilltoppers (4-2), Orlando Mendez-Valdez scored 13 on 7-of-8 shooting from the free-throw line. As a team, Western Kentucky shot 24-of-28 for 86 percent in free throws. Western Kentucky finishes the tournament 3-1, losing only to top-ranked Florida Friday night, while Ball State (2-3) ends 1-3 including a loss to No. 10 Kansas Friday night in the eight-team round-robin tournament. Julien Mills led Ball State with 17 points, going 5-of-6 from the free-throw line, where the Cardinals were 21-of-29 for 73 percent. Jalon Perryman added 13 points, and Micah Rollin had 12 points and eight rebounds. For the game, the Hilltoppers from the field shot 23-of-50 for 46 percent, while the Cardinals were 22-of-53 for 46 percent. From 3-point range, Ball State was 1-of-14 for 7 percent, while the Hilltoppers were 6-of-14 for 43 percent. After Ball State led 18-16 with 6:39 until halftime, the Hilltoppers ended the half on a 15-5 run and never trailed again. The Cardinals cut the halftime lead of 29-21 to 37-35 with 13:20 left, but got no closer.
